3. INFORMATION PROCESSED LOCALLY ON YOUR DEVICE

The App processes the following data exclusively on your device:

  a) URLs You Paste or Share
     When you paste a URL or share a link from another app, the URL is
     processed locally on your device to extract downloadable media. This
     URL is sent to the media extraction service (see Section 5) solely
     for the purpose of obtaining the direct download link. No URL is
     stored on our servers.

  b) Downloaded Media Files
     Videos, photos, and other media files you download are saved directly
     to your device's local storage in the folder "InstaReelsDownloader"
     within your device's public media directory. We do not upload, access,
     or transmit these files.

  c) In-App Browser Session (Private Mode)
     When you use the built-in browser to browse Instagram or other
     platforms, standard browser data (cookies, session tokens, cache) is
     stored locally on your device using Android's WebView component.
     We do NOT access, read, store, or transmit your Instagram login
     credentials or session tokens. This data is managed by Android's
     WebView and can be cleared from within the App or your device settings.

  d) Download History
     The App maintains a local list of your download history solely to
     display your past downloads within the App. This data is stored only
     on your device and is never transmitted to any server.

  e) App Preferences and Settings
     Any preferences you set within the App (such as download folder
     settings) are stored locally using Android SharedPreferences and
     are never transmitted.


4. PERMISSIONS USED AND WHY

The App requests the following Android permissions:

  INTERNET
  → Required to fetch and download media from URLs you provide.
    Without this permission, the App cannot function.

  READ_MEDIA_VIDEO / READ_MEDIA_IMAGES (Android 13+)
  READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (Android 12 and below)
  WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE (Android 9 and below)
  → Required to save downloaded videos and images to your device gallery
    and to display files you have already downloaded within the App.
    We do not read files beyond what you have downloaded using this App.

  FOREGROUND_SERVICE / FOREGROUND_SERVICE_DATA_SYNC
  → Required to run downloads in the background while you use other apps.
    This keeps downloads running even when the App is minimized.

  POST_NOTIFICATIONS
  → Required to show you download progress and completion notifications.
    You can disable these at any time in your device's notification settings.

  RECEIVE_BOOT_COMPLETED
  → Required to restore any pending downloads after your device restarts.
    This permission is used only to restart incomplete downloads, not to
    run the App continuously in the background.

  VIBRATE
  → Used to provide a brief vibration feedback when a download completes.

  No permissions are used to collect, track, or transmit personal data.


5. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES

The App uses the following third-party service to extract direct download
links from social media pages:

  a) SnapInsta / snapinsta.to (Media Extraction Service)
     When you request to download content from a URL, that URL is sent
     to the extraction service API at snapinsta.to to obtain a direct
     downloadable media link. Only the URL you provide is sent — no
     personal data, device identifiers, or account information is
     transmitted. Please review SnapInsta's own privacy policy at
     https://snapinsta.app/privacy-policy for details on how they
     handle URL requests.

  b) Glide (Image Loading Library)
     The App uses the Glide library (by Google/BumpTech) to display
     thumbnail images within the App. Glide processes images locally and
     does not transmit data to external servers.

  c) Android WebView (In-App Browser)
     The built-in browser uses Android's standard WebView component.
     WebView is governed by Android's own privacy and security framework.
     Any cookies or session data from websites you visit in the built-in
     browser are managed by Android's WebView and are not accessible to us.

The App does NOT integrate any of the following:
  • Google AdMob or any advertising SDK
  • Google Firebase (Analytics, Crashlytics, etc.)
  • Facebook Audience Network
  • Any social media login SDKs
  • Crash reporting services


